    <edge source="Based on the transcript, John Griffiths AM asked if maintaining at least the current level of funding would be guaranteed if the promises made during the Brexit referendum are kept. Eluned Morgan AM indicated that this would be a minimum, but there are other aspects to consider as well. The specific amount of funding was not mentioned in the transcript. Therefore, it is not possible to provide a precise amount for the expected funding. Moreover, the adequacy of this funding to address concerns about the shared prosperity fund is also not addressed in the transcript." target="1. Based on the transcript, the Welsh Government has not provided a specific funding commitment for the implementation of the Diamond and Reid reviews. However, Kirsty Williams AM has stated that the Welsh Government is fully committed to implementing the Diamond review proposals and has had discussions with HEFCW about their expectations for the implementation of Diamond. With regard to Reid, she mentioned that ongoing discussions are taking place within the government regarding the implementation of its recommendations. While they have not made a specific funding commitment, Kirsty Williams AM emphasized their commitment to implementing the Diamond review proposals and their intention to provide resources to institutions, as proposed by Diamond.">
