tudents. They are also improving international marketing of the HE sector, accessing resources under the European Transition Fund, Global Wales program, and other opportunities within the EU transition pot of money to boost international marketing of the HE sector and highlight its strengths.&#10;4. The impact of Brexit on higher education, further education, and apprenticeship provision is significant, regardless of a deal or no-deal Brexit scenario. Officials have visited individual institutions to discuss their preparedness for a 'no-deal' Brexit and are aware that funding for most HE activities is secured until December 2020 under a 'no-deal' scenario. However, the impact on research and apprenticeship provision beyond 2020 remains uncertain, as the broader economy and ability to work with companies locally and internationally may be affected by the relationship with the EU.">
